    ZINE
    Published by Vishal Kothari · 19 August 2018 ·

    Hello First Years!

    Zine - Robotics and Research group since its inception has been synonymous with excellence. Every year we conduct a workshop for first year students where we introduce the uninitiated to the captivating world of robotics over a span of 9 days.

    Here's what you will gain from this workshop:...
    ● We'll teach a host of interesting topics including robotics, coding, mechanical design, aeromodelling, app development, hacking and so much more!
    ● At Zine we believe that one learns best with hands-on experience. For this we'll conduct practicals and help you make your first ever bot!
    ● A starter kit including everything you need to start building a robot and yes you get to keep this one.
    ● A DVD containing awesome resources relating to what you will learn and for further learning.
    ● A certificate.

    Remember the registration ends in 4 days, so get a move on lest you miss this chance.

    Ciao,
    Team Zine

    ZINE
    Published by Devnath Nair · 15 August 2018 ·

    The wait is finally over and the REGISTRATION portal for ZINE WORKSHOP 2018 is live !

    A simple 2 step procedure is to be followed for registration :

    STEP 1: Register yourself on the app or the website, upon registering a unique ZINE ID will be generated. Capture a screenshot of that ID.

    ...

    STEP 2: Confirm your registration in person by paying the registration fee at the registration desk set up near Sports Complex.

    TIMINGS for fee payment:
    Weekdays - 5:15 to 7:00 PM
    holidays - 2:00 to 3:30 and 5:15 to 7:00 PM

    DATES for registrations and fee payment:
    15 - 22 August 2018

    VENUE : Near Sports Complex

    FEE : ₹900

    SO HURRY UP FOLKS GET YOURSELF REGISTERED ,THE CLOCK IS TICKING.

    APP: ZINE-robotics and research
    https://play.google.com/store/apps/details…

    WEBSITE: http://zine.co.in/

    ZINE
    Published by Vishal Kothari · 5 August 2018 ·

    “In Life, akin to computer code, There are people who are “ONES” and people who are “ZEROES”. People who act VS. people who don’t”

    Hello everyone!

    There's no doubt that you haven't heard about Zine by now. Some of you are probably wondering what the hype is all about. For the uninitiated 0.1%, allow us to enlighten you. Under the guidance of Dr.Rajesh Kumar, HoD Electrical Department; Zine has been the only active robotics and research group of MNIT for the past decade. We have participated and won in various national and international events related to a multitude of fields. Zine has proved time and again it’s excellence across a plethora of fields and is continously striving to attain new heights.
